cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about improving the accuracy and speed of visual tracking using Siamese networks. Siamese networks are commonly used in computer vision, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes new network architectures, which involves designing and optimizing neural networks, a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve tracking objects in videos, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the real-time aspect of the proposed methods, which is relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
